mental illness. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 27A-7 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: Any person serving as a member of a county board of mental illness, whose action regarding the applications or petitions for involuntary commitment or for the safekeeping otherwise of persons subject to involuntary commitment is taken in good faith, is immune from any civil liability that might otherwise be incurred or imposed. The immunity from civil liability under this section does not apply if injury results from gross negligence or willful or wanton misconduct. 500 copies of this document were printed by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.021 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 15497, "bill_version_id": 86435, "bill_version": "Senate Judiciary Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2000-02-16T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to provide immunity to members of county boards of mental illness and county review boards. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 27A-7 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: Any person serving as a member of a county board of mental illness, whose action regarding the applications or petitions for involuntary commitment or for the safekeeping otherwise of persons subject to involuntary commitment is taken in good faith, is immune from any civil liability that might otherwise be incurred or imposed. The immunity from civil liability under this section does not apply if injury results from gross negligence or willful or wanton misconduct. Section 2. That chapter 27B-7 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: Any person serving as a member of a county review board, whose action regarding the applications or petitions for involuntary commitment or for the safekeeping otherwise of persons subject to involuntary commitment is taken in good faith, is immune from any civil liability that might otherwise be incurred or imposed. The immunity from civil liability under this section does not apply if injury results from gross negligence or willful or wanton misconduct. BILL HISTORY 1/19/00 First read in House and referred to committee assignment waived. H.J. 138 1/20/00 Referred to Judiciary. 1/31/00 Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date. 1/31/00 Judiciary Deferred to another day. 2/2/00 Deferred by Chair. 2/4/00 Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date. 2/4/00 Judiciary Do Pass, Passed, AYES 9, NAYS 2. H.J. 412 2/7/00 House of Representatives Deferred to another day. H.J. 469 2/8/00 House of Representatives Do Pass, Passed, AYES 57, NAYS 8. H.J. 494 2/9/00 First read in Senate and referred to Judiciary. S.J. 399 2/16/00 Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date. 2/16/00 Judiciary Do Pass Amended, Passed, AYES 5, NAYS 1. S.J. 522"}, {"bill_id": 15497, "bill_version_id": 86433, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2000-02-23T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 15497, "action_date": "2000-01-19T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 85632, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/85632.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 138, "committee_id_action": 656, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 15497, "action_date": "2000-01-20T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 85634, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/85634.pdf", "status_text": "Referred to", "journal_page": 161, "committee_id_action": 656, "committee_id_assigned": 654, "result": "P", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 15497, "action_date": "2000-01-31T07:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 85814, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Document